ASEA Capital Corp BV is issuing a 10billion yen bond due April 23, 1992 carrying a coupon of 4-1/2pct and priced at 102-3/8, Mitsui Finance International Ltdsaid as lead manager.    The securities, which are guaranteed by parent company ASEACapital, will be listed on the Luxembourg Stock Exchange.    There is a put and a call option in 1990 at par. Thesecurities are available in denominations of one mln yen eachand are payable on April 23, 1987.    The company's outstanding issues are rated AA-minus byStandard and Poor's Corp.    There is a 1-1/4 pct selling concession and a 5/8 pctcombined management and underwriting fee. REUTER&#3;